From: Octopus Orchestrator upstream PR draft wave (M0-22)
Subject: [PATCH] cli: register `octo` as a top-level openclaw subcommand

Wire `openclaw octo` into the existing subcommand registry so the
Octopus Orchestrator CLI surface (status, mission, arm, grip, claims,
events, node, init, doctor — per LLD section Operator Surfaces) has a
dispatch entry point. Individual verb handlers land in later octo
milestones under src/octo/cli/octo-*.ts; this change adds only the
top-level registration.

Feature-flag gating (octo.enabled) is enforced inside the handler, not
at registration time, matching the pattern used by PR 1 (method list)
and PR 4 (slash command). When octo.enabled: false, the handler emits
a subsystem-specific error rather than Commander's default "unknown
command".

Draft authored against upstream commit 9ece252.

---
 src/cli/program/register.subclis.ts    | 5 +++++
 src/cli/program/subcli-descriptors.ts  | 5 +++++
 2 files changed, 10 insertions(+)

